verbs.description: overrule (third-person singular simple present overrules, present participle overruling, simple past and past participle overruled)

entries.meaning: (transitive) To rule over; to govern or determine by superior authority.
(transitive) To rule or determine in a contrary way; to decide against; to abrogate or alter.
(transitive) To nullify a previous ruling by a higher power.
examples: The line judge signalled the ball was in, but this was overruled by the umpire.

entries.meaning: (transitive, law) To dismiss or throw out (a protest or objection) at a court.
